<HEAD>Students Make Valentine's Day Pledge to Not Smoke</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEAUMONT, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   As part of an unusual Valentine's Day
project, about 350 students at two high schools have agreed to give
up or not start smoking or dipping snuff.
   The American Heart Association and the Texas Association of
Student Councils organized the project, called ``Save a Sweet
Heart,'' to make students aware of how cigarettes can affect their
hearts.
   About 250 students at West Brook Senior High and 96 at the
Central High School ninth-grade campus signed the pledges on Friday.
   The students themselves worked on promoting the day and
gathering pledges. The program is similar to the annual Great
American Smokeout that takes place in the fall.
